<br>
You mages that solo it without the epic pet at 49, 50, 51, 52, 53, 54 or 55 please clue me in on how your pet(s) absorb that much damage, while dealing out that much damage, and how you manage to have an unlimited supply of mana to chain cast pets and nuke without drawing aggro.<br>
<br>
I've noticed a LOT lately that people are saying &quot;Yeah, I solo'd mob_01 all night, was easy with my necro/shaman/druid/enchanter/cleric buddy&quot; or &quot;Yup, all you need is C2, SOW, buffs for your pet and you can solo it&quot;<br>
<br>
Errrm...solo means single.  <br>
<br>
It is quite amazing how fast the dino can make your top-of-the-line 51 earth summons, buffed, drop in HP from full to 25% in around 15seconds....all the while doing no noticable damage to the dino.  It's also great to land full damage LB, then realize you are around 15ish impossible more lava bolts away from a death blow.<br>
<br>
Yes, I'm real interested in how you folks &quot;solo&quot; it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udache79.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dache79</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#333333>(6/9/01 7:15:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=248.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing the Dino... ?</span><hr size=1> It's called pet recast.  Basically if the mob doesnt summon (not level 51) we mages can solo it.  I'm not going into pet recast here, there are posts all over on how to do it.<br>
