</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uthemadlimper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Mad Limper</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://gifs123.tripod.com/page11/monster10.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#333333>(6/9/01 5:02:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=248.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gifs123.tripod.com/page11/monster10.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing the Dino... ?</span><hr size=1> The only way I've ever been successful doing the dino camp is with help.  Prefered, 55 or higher shamy.  Alternate, 50 or higher necro and lastly 50 or higher cleric.<br>
<br>
My normal dino partner is a 56 shamy with the epic spear of fate.  He pulls with his slow spell, and I open with lava bolt to help get back aggro and sick in my 54 water pet.  Once dino leaves the shamy alone, he sicks his doggy on the dino's ass, and tosses out his uber disease spell (anti-regen), clicks his epic..which causes the dino to turn to his doggy, allowing my pet to start BS'ing.  I then usually cast 2 more lava bolts, spaced far apart to prevent aggro, while the shaman is clicking his JBB for all it's worth, and chloroblasting his pet when needed.  It usually takes right around a minute per fight, but does vary if dino decides to be resistant, which I then malise, and the occasional hard-aggro where one of us is running in small circles screaming hoping the other draws aggro.  This method usually leaves me around 40-50m, and the shamy 10-30m depending on how many heals needed.  Takes us around 5-6 minutes to get back to FM, rinse and repeat.  We have tried using just my pets to tank, using all...51 earth, 49/52 fire, 53 air and 54 water..and the shamy goes OOM healing my pets while I'm frantically chain casting them when they go below 15%.  Doable, but extremely unefecient.<br>
<br>
With a necro partner, it's fairly simple, with all of the pressure on the necro.  He must keep the dino engulfed 100% of the time, and feared around 80% of the time or the pets get chewed for lunch.  When the dino is gulping down the necro spells like candy, it's extremely easy.  When the dino decides to be a pain in the ass, he's a pain in the ass and if you survive those times, you are 9 times out of 10 OOM and medding for 10-12 minutes before next fight.  The fights usually take a while, in the 2+ minute range since the necro depletes his mana on engulf/fear and usually one DOT, while you are tasked with doing the big spell damage.  810dmg bolt doesn't dent the dino as much as one would hope/think.<br>
<br>
With a cleric partner, it's fairly easy to win, but the long downtime medding between fights gets to ya.  A cleric will have to CH my 58dmg hitting level 51 earth pet 5-7 times per fight, all the while I'm churning out lava bolts until I'm oom.  Using the water pet with a cleric isn't very safe, you really need your earth pet for root.  Jboots will keep you ahead of the dino, but if he starts tagging you, jboots only prolongs slightly your plight - it takes SOW to outrun the dino.  Fights take a long time, usually in the 2-4 minute range, and it gets real fun when the isle goblins start whacking on ya as you try to med between casts.<br>
<br>
For those of us who like to farm blue diamonds &amp; diamonds, the dino is a great way to do it, but get yourself a partner or it's not fun.  <br>
<br>
I firmly believe the dino has a special experience modifier as well.  OOT is generally a great exp zone, the un-named sisters, the aviaks, then the named sisters and dwarves, to Gornit and the seafurys.  But, the dino is super crappy exp.  At 54, I spent an entire day doing the dino with my shamy bud (56), we killed it 27 times.  The next day, I got the same amount of exp doing two rounds of the wizards/necro in 3rd gate (6 level 40 kills).  I believe VI changed the dino exp table to discourage spawn-camping for exp to level 60. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usalashpenumbra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salash Penumbra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 184<br> <font color=#333333>(6/9/01 5:12:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=248.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing the Dino... ?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> ...it takes SOW to outrun the dino</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
