<br>
Sit on the east side of the island so you can see the little totem where he likes to hang out some.  There is a long finger of land here to sit on. Make you pet and make around 4-5 levitate rings. Make sure you can eaisly get to the rings and reuse them. Burnout 3 pet and shield of lava him. Then go pull the dino.<br>
<br>
One thing I found never to do is to pull with any malo line spell. Its not worth it. You don't want the dino to be rooted much. The pet will draw enough aggro and land root some but the big killer is when the pet dies and the dino stays rooted he will regen pretty fast. So you don't want your pet to die with the dino rooted.<br>
<br>
Now you have him in tow take him to your pet and let him do his thing. Now soon as your pet is engaged RUN to the opposite side of the island and sit as close to the water as you can and med. Have your pet on target. Soon as your pet dies resummon put on lava shield and med until he comes. Sic pet and run back to the opposite side where you started. Rinse and repeat.<br>
<br>
At lvl 49 you will not have enough mana to keep doing this until he is dead. So when you are low on mana and can't summon a pet run around the edge of the island with the dino in pursuit stop when you can and med a tick or 2 then get up and keep running. While running click on your pet spell to see if you have enough mana if you do you will start casting but will be interrupted. At this time make at least one full run around the island then stop and turn around and cast your pet spell. You should have enough time to pop out a pet then run and med again. Keep this up and you will down the dino. In all it can take around half an hour or so to kill him depending on your mana pool.<br>
<br>
Now thats how you can solo him at 49. Btw you have to have levi on to get any real distance from him with jboots. Also phantom armor line is a real help as I always ended up getting hit a few a times. He is not really worth the effort to solo, just take another mage or a necro with you and kill him.<br>
